CLIFFORD L. WICKMAN v. CYRIL BOHLE [No. 81,

October Term, 1937.]

*696Decided January 13th, 1938.

The cause was argued before Bond, C. J., Urner, Opputt, Parke, Sloan, Mitchell, Shehan, and Johnson, JJ.

Roscoe C. Rowe, with whom was C. Ferdinand Sybert on the brief, for the appellant. J. Gilbert Prendergast and Roszel C. Thomsen, with whom were James Clark and Walter L. Clark, on the brief, for the appellee. Bond, C. J.,

delivered the opinion of the Court.
